reviews.title: Keep coming back
reviews.text:
Lunched and ate here several times and delicious every time! 
The meal salads are something we come back for every time and the ribs are very tasty (while I am very picky about them)!
Recommended! The staff is also friendly.

reviews.title: Delicious and cozy
reviews.text:
Super restaurant in a cozy place. We both had the tournedous stroganoff and this one was butter tender.
The salad and the special looking kind of ribbed fries was also tasteful.
Breadboard beforehand was generous with plenty of sauces.
Will definitely be back.

reviews.title: Good location and nice restaurant!
reviews.text: Lovely place right in the center near the beautiful church. Good service and good food for a nice price. Definitely worth a visit.

reviews.title: A ten!
reviews.text: Perfect terrace with evening sun. Friendly service and friendly staff. Food Exceptional! , quality meat/fish. Cozy location in the center of Epe. Worth repeating 👌

reviews.title: Fantastic restaurant!
reviews.text:
This restaurant is fantastic! Rarely eaten such a delicious Japanese Salmon teriyaki.
Nice tent, friendly service. Will definitely come back here again!

reviews.title: Perfect lunch and excellent service
reviews.text: Inside completely renovated, beautiful atmospheric business (outside we still doubted, but just walk inside). We ordered loaded fries and n steak sandwich. We hadn't had them that good. Now we also understood why it was so busy in the business, next time Epen we will definitely come back here.

reviews.title: Delicious!
reviews.text: Fine restaurant: great food, generous portions and nice atmosphere. The staff was nice and relaxed. I will definitely be back here again!

reviews.title: Less experience
reviews.text: We have eaten here before and until today it was always good. Today was a lesser experience. Reheated satay of the tenderloin resulting in very dry pork tenderloin. The service also preferred to be at the bar rather than occasionally come to the tables to ask if everything was satisfactory.

reviews.title: Food
reviews.text: We ordered from the baron but we got the wrong food We told that to the waiter only the waiter wanted to be right but the people further down the bar have kindly solved it

reviews.title: Coincidence exists
reviews.text:
We decided to go shopping in Epe on Saturday. A village that we mainly know from a tent holiday on the Veluwe long ago.
At lunchtime we already had a bag full, time for coffee.
It was pleasantly busy with all the old cars along the street and a music system at the church, which only played pop music from the late 60s and early 70s. This made the atmosphere a bit old-fashioned in the village.
Perched on the terrace at the Baron. Hospitable service, 2 delicious coffees with a liqueur and whipped cream and pastries. We sat close to the loudspeaker and heard, among other things, Long Cool Woman (In a Black Dress) by the Hollies. When we got back into the car 10 minutes later, the first song we heard on the radio was Long Cool Woman (In a Black Dress) again. Coincidence exists.

reviews.title: Do not order tomato soup! Too salty too spicy
reviews.text: Last year on holiday we always had tomato soup at the Baron, last time the soup was unedible, so spicy and salty, now we are on holiday again and the waiter asked if the soup was better, it would be tested, once served (by another employee) it was again unpalatable, so salty and spicy, we left everything including drinks and paid for it and will never see us again, good luck with the business

reviews.title: Delicious food, the service can be better.
reviews.text: We have been sitting here on the terrace this afternoon and have a few drinks. Afterwards we have dined here with six persons. The food was not only very beautiful to see, but also super tasty. As a point of attention, the young waitress must learn how to serve. She put all the drinks directly in front of her and you had to take what you had ordered yourself. That is a bit weird. But ..... the food (also vegetarian) is really recommended.

reviews.title: great area
reviews.text: The food is good only I've been sitting there a few times Around 5 o'clock and Then you have to wait a lot of telang for service I just walked away and went to the neighbors worthless here has to change costs your customers I've been around for a long time but you can improve your greetings Lilian

reviews.title: Good place for coffee!
reviews.text: At De Baron I had coffee or tea at a number of occasions. You can sit and talk at a nice and quiet table or at the terrace. Friendly staff!

reviews.title: Simple food offer at a decent price
reviews.text:
This brown cafe style "lunch\dinner solution" is a simple centre town location with an easy menu choice.
Nothing fancy , nothing special , but good enough to frequent, if you have no time\possibillity to cook yourselves.
